project.name: Outwave.js
project.description: Web based waveform viewer, supporting long recordings

TimeSpan.name: TimeSpan
TimeSpan.description: Adds support for marking time spans(segments) of waveform

ContinuousTimeSpanCollection.name: ContinuousTimeSpanCollection
ContinuousTimeSpanCollection.description:
Continuous time span collection

Manages all time spans

Draggable.name: Draggable
Draggable.description: Mixin that adds dragging capability to time spans

SparseTimeSpanCollection.name: SparseTimeSpanCollection
SparseTimeSpanCollection.description:
Continuous time span collection

Manages all time spans

TimeSpanCollection.name: TimeSpanCollection
TimeSpanCollection.description:
Manages time spans

Abstract class - use subclasses

TimeSpan.name: TimeSpan
TimeSpan.description:
Represents time span

Abstract class - use subclasses

Controls.name: Controls
Controls.description:
Adds control buttons to waveform viewer

Use without new keyword

DataFile.name: DataFile
DataFile.description:
Waveform data and methods for getting samples

Use static method loadUrl for getting a DataFile from a URL directly

params.name: dataView
params.description: DataView or compatible(jDataView) of waveform file

Outwave.name: Outwave
Outwave.description:
Waveform viewer loader
Loads datafile and creates a waveform viewer instance. Adds control buttons if enabled in options.
If no errors occur onLoad is called with the viewer instance as an argument

Use without new keyword

params.name: onLoad
params.description: Function(Viewer viewer) - viewer has been successfully loaded

Viewer.name: Viewer
Viewer.description:
Main waveform viewer object

Width and height(x,y) dimensions are used as if for horizontal orientation.
If you are using Outwave vertically, exchange the dimensions. Eg. the height option means width on screen.

params.name: container
params.description: The element which the viewer will reside in
